      <section class="main-section" id="Why_Bother?">
        <header id="Why_Bother?">Why bother?</header>
        <p>Why should you even care? Nobody else does right?</p>
        <p>What does that matter? Why would we even have to begin to consider what somebody else thinks. You shouldn't think of them with negative things, so don't bring them into your positive goals.</p>
      </section>
      <section class="main-section" id="Diet">
        <header id="Diet">Diet</header>
        <p>This really is the back bone of so much of your improvement. Helping energy levels, skin condition, gut health and of course weight. Areas of focus may be: </p>
        <li>Increase your protein intake</li>
        <li>Lower your carb intake</li>
        <li>Increase your water intake</li>
      </section>
      <section class="main-section" id="Exercise">
        <header id="Exercise">Exercise</header>
        <p>Time to get into the nitty gritty. We'll start slowly, easing into less familiar exercises that are going to target your goals and boost your confidence.</p>
        <p>Don't feel that pressure to rush off. Consistency is everything. As Tony Robins said, and I'm paraphrasing here, "Most people overestimate what they can achieve in a year, and wildly underestimate what they can achieve in a lifetime. There's time." You might split your week over 3 days of exercise, e.g.:</p>
        <li>Mon: Legs</li>
        <li>Wed: Torso + Cardio</li>
        <li>Fri: HIIT</li>

      </section>
      <section class="main-section" id="Goals">
        <header id="Goals">Goals</header>
        <p>Here we want to be crystal clear we precisely what we don't want to happen, and what we do want to happen. Carrot and stick. I can't reccomend enough as some extra homework, going away and sitting through Jordan Peterson's Future Authoring Programme. Takes maybe a couple of hours, but it'll set you on the right path for life.</p>
      </section>
      <section class="main-section" id="Hobbies">
        <header id="Hobbies">Hobbies</header>
        <p>Here you want these to do two things. Entertain you. Reflect something about you. For instance my main one is Scuba Diving. It takes a full half day to get a decent one in from where I am and it's my favourite place in the world to be. It's also taken patience and frugality to learn and save for the courses and equipment to make myself self sufficient. This reflects well in a CV or job interview or just when making conversation as it shows desirable skills people hope to emulate or share in.</p>
        <code></code>
