        <code></code>
      </section>
      <section class="main-section" id="Clothing">
        <header id="Clothing">Clothing</header>
        <p>Here again we'll need to outsource to greater minds than mine. I myself lean heavily on my wife to guide me in this instance. But before her it was apps, blogs and friends.</p>
        <p>As a part of your goal setting you'll have come to understand an idea of how you want to present to the world. Perhaps your new wardrobe is the best way to begin reflecting this.</p>
        <li>Find inspiration</li>
        <li>Focus on what it is you like about it</li>
        <li>Make it your own</li>
      </section>
      <section class="main-section" id="Moving_Forward">
        <header id="Moving_Forward">Moving Forward</header>
        <p>That's it for now. Just a few areas to get yourself started. The keen will think to jump straight in and get it all done in an evening, leave the notpad on the side or tucked safely on your desktop. To never look at it again.</p>
        <p>I'd suggest scheduling. Open up your google calender and set yourself 30min tasks to work on each of them, perhaps every morning as a way to start a new early bird schedule to get shit done before anyone else is even awake. Now go get 'em.</p>
      </section>
